A reckless driver ignored 'road closed' signs and drove through a swollen ford - and ended up on top of another stricken car.

The road in Hinxton, South Cambridgeshire, had been closed due to high water levels which had already caused a Volvo car to get stuck in the river.

But the driver of a Vauxhall ignored the warnings and drove into the flood water - only to be swept onto the roof of the Volvo.

