The iridescent colours are due to the ice crystals being of a uniform shape and size and the cloud covering being thin.

The sun has to be at just the right angle below the horizon to cause diffraction and interference with the crystals to produce the beautiful colours.

Scientists believe the clouds also help accelerate the process of the depletion of the ozone layer.

The clouds provide a surface for the chlorine and bromine in CFC’s to react into an active form, which makes the chlorine more destructive to the ozone layer.

